<paragraph blockId="33.[151,1437,1286,1853]" pageId="33" pageNumber="543">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,330,1575,1601]" pageId="33" pageNumber="543">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
Examination of the 
<typeStatus box="[558,656,1575,1601]" pageId="33" pageNumber="543">holotype</typeStatus>
and its comparison with species of 
<taxonomicName box="[1056,1180,1575,1601]" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Agathocles" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="543" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1056,1180,1575,1601]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="543">Agathocles</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1861" box="[1235,1335,1575,1601]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Caystrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="543" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1235,1335,1575,1601]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="543">Caystrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
revealed that it markedly differs from the first genus and fits well the second one, especially in having the body short, more regularly oval and relatively flat, head relatively short, mandibular plates not expanded forward and strongly narrowing anteriad, pronotum with sharp margins, and pale brown dorsal colouration with longitudinal yellowish unpunctured lines along corial veins (cf. 
<figureCitation box="[613,772,1718,1745]" captionStart="FIGURES 125–129" captionStartId="36.[151,264,1665,1689]" captionTargetBox="[167,1417,192,1642]" captionTargetId="figure-19@36.[167,1420,181,1642]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIGURES 125–129. Caystrus dubius (Distant, 1921), comb. nov., holotype, female: 125–126—habitus (125—dorsal view, 126—ventral view); 127—external scent efferent system of metathoracic scent gland; 128—external female genitalia, caudal view; 129—labels. Orig. P. Kment." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4692419" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4692419/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="543">Figs 125–126</figureCitation>
). Therefore, we transfer this species to the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1861" box="[1330,1430,1719,1745]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Caystrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="543" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1330,1430,1719,1745]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="543">Caystrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, resulting in a new combination: 
<taxonomicName authority="(Distant, 1921)" authorityName="Salini &amp; Kment" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Distant" baseAuthorityYear="1921" box="[538,912,1755,1781]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Caystrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="543" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dubius" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[538,724,1755,1781]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="543">Caystrus dubius</emphasis>
(Distant, 1921)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[929,1062,1755,1781]" pageId="33" pageNumber="543">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[929,1062,1755,1781]" pageId="33" pageNumber="543" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
We did not find any important differences between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Salini &amp; Kment" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Distant" baseAuthorityYear="1921" box="[384,492,1791,1817]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Caystrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="543" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dubius">
<emphasis box="[384,492,1791,1817]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="543">C. dubius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Distant" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[548,682,1791,1817]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Caystrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="543" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obscurus">
<emphasis box="[548,682,1791,1817]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="543">C. obscurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but we leave the decision on their synonymy for a furure revision of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1861" box="[182,282,1827,1853]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Caystrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="543" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[182,282,1827,1853]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="543">Caystrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
